  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kalinga at Alaga para sa Ligtas na Komunidad: Building a Community Health, Safety, &amp; Support System</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By mainstreaming harm reduction framework as the alternative to the national government&#x2019;s &#x201C;war on drugs,&#x201D; the local government officials and community leaders would be equipped with a public health and human rights perspectives on addressing the drug situation. The conduct of capacity-building training and mentoring on harm reduction with local government officials and urban poor leaders provides an opportunity to produce local champions/ advocates for harm reduction, which would help in creating a strong support base at the ground level, necessary for the implementation of the project.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will: 1) provide an alternative framework to address the drug situation by mainstreaming harm reduction among local government officials and communities; and, 2) support the development of community-based health intervention program for persons who use drugs (PWUD) by training community facilitators in partner Local Government Units (LGUs) using pre-tested modules on Harm Reduction developed by CA partner Institute of Politics and Governance (IPG) in pilot communities and will be enhanced based on the experience in the pilot sites and new areas for the project. The project will link LGUs and PWUDs with advocates/ practitioners of the harm reduction approach and other social service providers through a referral network and support system.</narrative>
  </description>
